Title: 2013 Ford Focus manual (economic & fuel efficient)
Body: I am Selling my 2013 Ford Focus for $4200. No trades only cash offers. The vehicle has a manual transmission with a total of 68307 miles and a clean title. The manual transmission makes this car great for daily commuters or students on a budget. I personally used this car to commute to and from UTEP and it saved me a great deal at the pumps.

The vehicle is in good running condition and has been well maintained with frequent oil changes, recent replacement of the front brake pads and tire rotations, AC and heat are good. Other than replacing the battery the vehicle has not experienced any major mechanical issues. Overall the car is in great shape, but with any used car there tends to be small blemishes, I would like to address these. There is a scratch on the backseat inside passenger window, the drivers side taillight has a small hole (about a quarter sized, still works) and one of the four air vents on the dashboard stopped blowing air. There are also two safety recalls for parts on this vehicle. The first is a door locking mechanism, I have yet to experience any issues with it. The second is a CPV (canister purge valve) within the fuel vapor system, which will also need to be inspected, I have not experienced any issues with either recalls. Both recalls can be replaced at the Casa Ford dealership or any Ford dealership for free. I have not had the time to visit the dealership but I have spoken with representatives and was told it is a simple repair and will take less than a day again for free.

Title: 2012 Ford E150 Wheelchair Mobility Hi-Top Van, WARRANTY! See Video!
Body: 2012 Ford E150 Hi-Top Wheelchair Handicap Van with warranty!

Here is a wheelchair van that is in superb condition, is very nicely equipped, and comes with a 3-year, unlimited mileage warranty on the engine! As the pictures and video illustrate, this van is just the right mix of size and features that can suit your needs just right! This van has a tall roof like a bus, allowing you to stand comfortably in the van, yet it doesn't have the large size of a bus that makes parking and maneuvering difficult. Just like a larger bus, you still have seating for up to 5 passengers, yet its size is nimble enough to easily drive in parking lots, alley ways, and park inside garages.

The powertrain on this van features the Triton 5.4L gasoline engine and an automatic overdrive transmission. The engine ignites right away (see video), it idles very quiet and smooth, and it quickly gets this van up to highway speeds. All the gears on the automatic overdrive transmission engage properly, they pull strong, and they shift smoothly. The overall drive on this van is commendable; the acceleration is strong, the suspension feels very snug, the ride is straight, the braking is even, and the interior is quiet at highway speeds (see video).

A noteworthy feature on this van is the engine. The engine was very recently installed and has less than 1,000 miles on it! Furthermore, this engine comes with a 3 year, unlimited nationwide warranty! Talk about peace of mind!

The body on this truck speaks volumes about the life this van has experienced; the original paint is shiny and healthy, all the bodylines are straight, there is no rust or structural damage, and the overall appearance is outstanding! All the doors open and close effortlessly, there are no cracks on the glass, all the exterior lighting is fully functional, and the trim is in like new condition. The interior of this van is also in exceptional condition! The floor, the seats, the moldings, and the trim are in virtually new condition. All the interior lighting is fully functional, the rear AC blows remarkably well, and the interior literally still smells like new! This van has all the hallmarks of a vehicle that has been lightly used and been on the highway most of the time!

As the video illustrates, the Braun Century 2 Wheelchair lift is in optimal operating condition. The lift unfolds, descends, rises, and folds smoothly. There are no leaks on any of the hydraulic cylinders, hoses, or pump. The physical condition of the lift is beyond reproach, with no structural damage or corrections, straight lines, and a very pleasant appearance. We tested this lift by having three grown men stand on it (approximately 700 lbs!) and the lift functioned properly every time!

Title: 2016 Ford F-150, F 150, F150  Low Miles
1919 Ford Model T Touring
Body: Up for Sale: 1919 Ford Model T Touring Car.
I bought this in Arizona and put it back together, a very solid Car.
Complete and with numbers matching, built May of 1919 (100 years old).
1919 was the first year for electric start and bolt on rims (no need to crank this old car).
Accessories; 8 day wind up clock (rebuilt), running board luggage rack, fender tool box.
This is NO hot rod, she is very stock with only some nicer modifications (brake light added).
Every car has a story, and this is no exception.
My Mother’s side of the family’s first car was a 1919 Ford Model T, just like this.

My Grandmother took her 2 Sisters into town for a little trip. On the way home she tore the front fender off when she hit a bridge. She never drove again…. She lived to be 103 and her name was Elisabeth (Lizzy).

The Bad news; The tires on the car are weathered, the paint is not show quality (it has some chips and some repairs that don’t match exactly). And if you didn’t know it leaks a bit, like all Model T’s do.
We have enjoyed driving this when ever we could, but sadly we now only take her out for Halloween. And the fact that I have some 28 other cars and scooters, so I am putting her up for sale.
$14,000.00 Cash and drive home (although it might take some time if you live far away, top speed is 36 MPH). or trailer it home.
If you have never driven a Model T, I can teach you.
